<body id="bg">
    @* <div class="header-img"><img src="~/images/main-slider/header.webp" alt="Header Image" /></div> *@
    <div class="blog-main-container m-t90">
        <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">
            <h3 class="subheading">New 2025 Maruti Suzuki Dzire: A Fresh Take on the Compact Sedan</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/front.webp" alt="Rear Parking Sensor" title="Rear Parking Sensor" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>Maruti Suzuki has unveiled the 2025 Dzire, a compact sedan that blends modern aesthetics with advanced features, setting new benchmarks in its segment. With a refreshed design, upgraded technology, and improved efficiency, the new Dzire is poised to maintain its dominance in the Indian market.</p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Stylish and Elegant Design</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/side_view.webp" alt="side" title="side" /></div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/headlamps.webp" alt="headlamps" title="headlamps" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>The 2025 Dzire features a redesigned front fascia, including a sleek hexagonal grille with chrome accents, LED projector headlamps, and a sportier bumper design. The profile remains sophisticated with sculpted lines, new diamond-cut alloy wheels, and a coupe-like silhouette. At the rear, the updated LED tail lamps add a touch of premium appeal.</p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Premium and Tech-Loaded Interiors</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/dual_tone_interior.webp" alt="interior" title="interior" /></div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/electric_sunroof.webp" alt="sunroof" title="sunroof" /></div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/automatic_climate_control.webp" alt="automatic_climate_control" title="automatic_climate_control" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>Step inside, and you’ll find an enhanced cabin with beige upholstery, a dark brown dashboard accented by silver trims, and faux wood inserts. The biggest highlight is the<span class="font-weight-700"> 9-inch Smartplay Pro Plus infotainment system, </span> which supports wireless Apple CarPlay and Android Auto. Additionally, the car comes equipped with Maruti Suzuki’s <span class="font-weight-700">connected car technology, </span>offering remote vehicle access, live tracking, and safety alerts. Higher trims also feature a factory-fitted <span class="font-weight-700">sunroof, </span> a first for the Dzire.</p>
            <p>Other notable features include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Automatic climate control</li>
                <li>Cruise control</li>
                <li>Rear AC vents</li>
                <li>Rear center armrest</li>
                <li>Push-button start/stop</li>
                <li>A 360-degree camera (top trims)</li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="subheading">Powertrain and Fuel Efficiency</h3>
            <p>Under the hood, the Dzire is powered by a<span class="font-weight-700"> 1.2-litre, three-cylinder Z12E petrol engine, </span> delivering <span class="font-weight-700">82 HP and 112 Nm of torque, </span>paired with an idle start/stop feature for enhanced fuel efficiency. The sedan offers two transmission choices: a <span class="font-weight-700">5-speed manual and a 5-speed AMT. </span></p>
            <p>For eco-conscious buyers, <span class="font-weight-700">CNG variants</span> are also available, producing<span class="font-weight-700"> 69.75 HP and 101.8 Nm of torque. </span>Fuel efficiency figures are impressive:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">24.79 km/l</span> (manual petrol variant)</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">25.71 km/l</span> (AMT petrol variant)</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">33.73 km/kg</span> (CNG variant)</li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="subheading">Enhanced Safety Standards</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/airbags.webp" alt="airbags" title="airbags" /></div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/back.webp" alt="back" title="back" /></div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/rear_ac_vent.webp" alt="rear" title="rear" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>The 2025 Dzire has been awarded a <span class="font-weight-700">5-star rating for adult occupant protection</span> and <span class="font-weight-700">4-star rating for child occupant protection</span> by Global NCAP. Standard safety features include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Six airbags</span></li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Electronic Stability Program (ESP)</span></li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Hill hold assist</span></li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">ABS with EBD and brake assist</span></li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">ISOFIX child seat mounts</span></li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Rear parking sensors and camera</span></li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="subheading">Variants and Pricing</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/feb/marutisuzukidzire2025/magmagrey.webp" alt="magmagrey" title="magmagrey" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>The new Dzire is available in <span class="font-weight-700">four trims:</span> LXi, VXi, ZXi, and ZXi+, with CNG options offered on the VXi and ZXi trims. Pricing starts at  <span class="font-weight-700">₹6.79 lakh, </span> going up to  <span class="font-weight-700">₹10.14 lakh</span> for the top-spec model. Additionally, Maruti Suzuki’s  <span class="font-weight-700">subscription plans </span>start from <span class="font-weight-700"> ₹18,248 per month</span>  for added flexibility.</p>
